  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Step 1: Cuts and Pocket Holes",
      "body": "Make Cuts and create pocket holes where indicated by the red dots in the provided cut list. However, I do suggest cutting as you go in order to keep the project square."
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 2: Form Box",
      "body": "Using the 2 side panels and 1 shelf, attach the bottom shelf to the side panels with 1 1/4\" pocket hole screws and wood glue.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/fde0b6ae476643fb.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 3: Attach Top Supports",
      "body": "Attach top support boards to side panels using 1 1/4\" Pocket Hole Screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/25315f031ebe899e.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 4: Add Bottom Trim",
      "body": "Add the bottom trim to the bottom, flush with the side panels using wood glue and 1 1/4\" finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/797b7350ff420739.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 5: Add Shelf",
      "body": "Attach cleats using wood glue and 1 1/4\" finish nails. Secure shelf to top of cleats with wood glue and 1 1/4\" finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/68c405fb762db427.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 6: Attach Facing",
      "body": "Build the facing with 1 1/4\" pocket holes and then attach facing to side panels using the pre drilled pocket holes in the side panels and pocket holes at the bottom of the side facings.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/faa9a229876407ad.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 7: Attach Back Panel",
      "body": "Attach Back Panel with 1/2\" finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/bdad49ad96ee9de2.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 8: Attach top",
      "body": "Join the (2) 1\" x 10\" x 32 1/2\" boards with 1 1/4\" Pocket Hole Screws and wood glue. Attach the top to the side panels with pre drilled pocket holes in the side panels.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/09b6f71d7a4e08af.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 9: Build Door",
      "body": "Build door by attaching the 2\" plywood strips to the 1/2\" panel with wood glue and 1/2\" finish nails.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d3f2e2fc7b53fa3c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Step 10: Add Hardware",
      "body": "Attach the door with your T hinges leaving an 1/8\" gap around the perimeter of the door. Then attach the sliding barrel bolt to the door. Finish with your desired style and enjoy!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/f05c9a8a75695328.webp"
    }
  ],
